event: response.reasoning_summary_text.done
data: {"type":"response.reasoning_summary_text.done","item_id":"rs_033a97a9e38891b10169e3dc2ca0188194aef0f79e4aa9e4fd","output_index":0,"sequence_number":241,"summary_index":1,"text":"**Planning a low-crowd Kyoto experience**\n\nI want to suggest visiting Arashiyama early to avoid midday crowds, particularly the bamboo grove or Togetsukyo bridge. Choosing weekdays over weekends could help, and starting around 7:00 AM is ideal. For cultural experiences, I could recommend a \"Kyoto Cooking Class\" but also suggest watching a Maiko rehearsal or visiting Kodai-ji for budget-friendly options. Other ideas include tea ceremonies and Nishijin Weaving Studio experiences. I'll ensure to include public baths, local street food, and essential temples like Fushimi Inari, Tofuku-ji, and Myoshin-ji, prioritizing low entry fees."}

event: response.reasoning_summary_part.done
data: {"type":"response.reasoning_summary_part.done","item_id":"rs_033a97a9e38891b10169e3dc2ca0188194aef0f79e4aa9e4fd","output_index":0,"part":{"type":"summary_text","text":"**Planning a low-crowd Kyoto experience**\n\nI want to suggest visiting Arashiyama early to avoid midday crowds, particularly the bamboo grove or Togetsukyo bridge. Choosing weekdays over weekends could help, and starting around 7:00 AM is ideal. For cultural experiences, I could recommend a \"Kyoto Cooking Class\" but also suggest watching a Maiko rehearsal or visiting Kodai-ji for budget-friendly options. Other ideas include tea ceremonies and Nishijin Weaving Studio experiences. I'll ensure to include public baths, local street food, and essential temples like Fushimi Inari, Tofuku-ji, and Myoshin-ji, prioritizing low entry fees."},"sequence_number":242,"summary_index":1}

