event: response.reasoning_summary_text.done
data: {"type":"response.reasoning_summary_text.done","item_id":"rs_033a97a9e38891b10169e3dc2ca0188194aef0f79e4aa9e4fd","output_index":0,"sequence_number":391,"summary_index":2,"text":"**Crafting a free garden itinerary**\n\nI’m focusing on gardens, but many have an entry fee. Let's structure a three-day plan to minimize transit. For Day 1, I might start in Arashiyama, visiting Sagano and Otagi Nenbutsu-ji for fewer crowds, plus Tenryu-ji, despite its fee. Day 2 would focus on Central East, starting with Fushimi Inari in the morning, then Toji and Tofuku-ji. I could suggest a Sake brewery tour in Fushimi as a cultural experience. For Day 3, I’ll explore low-crowd temples in Northern Kyoto, starting with Ninna-ji. A hike to Kurama/Kibune might be a nice fit too!"}

