data: {"type":"response.reasoning_summary_part.done","item_id":"rs_033a97a9e38891b10169e3dc2ca0188194aef0f79e4aa9e4fd","output_index":0,"part":{"type":"summary_text","text":"**Finalizing Kyoto itinerary with cultural experiences**\n\nI’m looking at including a small fee for the temple hall access, possibly around 500 yen. We’ll mention important sake museums like the Gekkeikan Okura and possibly Kubota or Tsukasa, noting that Gekkeikan might cost around 1000 yen for entry.  \n\nFor Day 3, I'll suggest Shimogamo and Kamigamo Shrines, then head to Kurama and Kibune, where Kurama Onsen could be an optional stop. I'll focus on creating a budget-friendly itinerary while clustering sights to minimize travel and walking instead of using taxis."},"sequence_number":882,"summary_index":6}

